          </div>
          <div class="timeline-row">
            <span class="yr">2024</span>
            <span class="desc">Moderate adjustment</span>
            <span class="amt">$14,600</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-row current">
            <span class="yr">2025</span>
            <span class="desc">Official IRS amount</span>
            <span class="amt">$15,000</span>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-row proj-row-t">
            <span class="yr">2026</span>
            <span class="desc">Projected (~2.5% adj.)</span>
            <span class="amt">~$15,500</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="info-callout">
          <p><strong>Why projections vary:</strong> Tax analysts project the standard deduction using C-CPI-U data from August of the prior year through August of the current year. The exact amount rounds to the nearest $50 per IRS rounding rules. Final figures are announced in the IRS revenue procedure each fall.</p>
        </div>
